{
    "publish_date": "2012-04-16T15:13:02.000Z", 
    "video_length": "PT5M28S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "You probably already know", 
            "dur": "1.2", 
            "start": "13.809"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "everything is made up\nof little tiny things called atoms", 
            "dur": "2.69", 
            "start": "15.033"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or even that each atom\nis made up of even smaller particles", 
            "dur": "2.961", 
            "start": "17.747"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "called protons, neutrons and electrons.", 
            "dur": "2.122", 
            "start": "20.732"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And you&#39;ve probably heard\nthat atoms are small.", 
            "dur": "2.287", 
            "start": "22.878"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But I bet you haven&#39;t ever thought\nabout how small atoms really are.", 
            "dur": "4.16", 
            "start": "25.189"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, the answer is\nthat they are really, really small.", 
            "dur": "3.716", 
            "start": "29.373"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So you ask, just how small are atoms?", 
            "dur": "3.039", 
            "start": "33.908"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "To understand this,\nlet&#39;s ask this question:", 
            "dur": "3.073", 
            "start": "36.971"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "How many atoms are in a grapefruit?", 
            "dur": "1.908", 
            "start": "40.068"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, let&#39;s assume that the grapefruit\nis made up of only nitrogen atoms,", 
            "dur": "3.429", 
            "start": "42.721"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which isn&#39;t at all true, but there\nare nitrogen atoms in a grapefruit.", 
            "dur": "3.658", 
            "start": "46.174"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "To help you visualize this,\nlet&#39;s blow up each of the atoms", 
            "dur": "3.031", 
            "start": "49.856"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to the size of a blueberry.", 
            "dur": "1.813", 
            "start": "52.911"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And then how big\nwould the grapefruit have to be?", 
            "dur": "3.148", 
            "start": "54.748"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It would have to be the same size of\n-- well, actually, the Earth.", 
            "dur": "4.029", 
            "start": "57.92"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That&#39;s crazy!", 
            "dur": "1.016", 
            "start": "61.973"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You mean to say that if I filled\nthe Earth with blueberries,", 
            "dur": "2.821", 
            "start": "63.013"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I would have the same number\nof nitrogen atoms as a grapefruit?", 
            "dur": "2.977", 
            "start": "65.858"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That&#39;s right!", 
            "dur": "1", 
            "start": "68.859"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So how big is the atom?", 
            "dur": "1.533", 
            "start": "70.258"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, it&#39;s really, really small!", 
            "dur": "1.741", 
            "start": "72.761"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And you know what?\nIt gets even more crazy.", 
            "dur": "2.435", 
            "start": "75.541"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s now look inside of each atom\n-- and thus the blueberry, right? --", 
            "dur": "3.773", 
            "start": "78"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What do you see there?", 
            "dur": "1.113", 
            "start": "81.797"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In the center of the atom\nis something called the nucleus,", 
            "dur": "2.721", 
            "start": "82.934"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which contains protons and neutrons,", 
            "dur": "1.727", 
            "start": "85.679"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and on the outside, you&#39;d see electrons.", 
            "dur": "2.061", 
            "start": "87.43"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So how big is the nucleus?", 
            "dur": "1.461", 
            "start": "89.515"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If atoms are like blueberries\nin the Earth,", 
            "dur": "2.135", 
            "start": "91.381"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "how big would the nucleus be?", 
            "dur": "1.777", 
            "start": "93.54"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You might remember the old pictures\nof the atom from science class,", 
            "dur": "3.217", 
            "start": "95.341"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "where you saw this tiny dot on the page\nwith an arrow pointing to the nucleus.", 
            "dur": "3.763", 
            "start": "98.582"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, those pictures,\nthey&#39;re not drawn to scale,", 
            "dur": "2.395", 
            "start": "102.369"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "so they&#39;re kind of wrong.", 
            "dur": "1.615", 
            "start": "104.788"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So how big is the nucleus?", 
            "dur": "1.556", 
            "start": "106.427"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So if you popped open the blueberry\nand were searching for the nucleus ...", 
            "dur": "3.969", 
            "start": "108.007"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You know what? It would be invisible.", 
            "dur": "2.246", 
            "start": "113.236"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s too small to see!", 
            "dur": "1.642", 
            "start": "115.506"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "OK. Let&#39;s blow up the atom --\nthe blueberry --", 
            "dur": "2.776", 
            "start": "117.944"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to the size of a house.", 
            "dur": "1.232", 
            "start": "120.744"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So imagine a ball that is as tall\nas a two-story house.", 
            "dur": "3.738", 
            "start": "122"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s look for the nucleus\nin the center of the atom.", 
            "dur": "2.477", 
            "start": "125.762"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And do you know what?\nIt would just barely be visible.", 
            "dur": "3.295", 
            "start": "128.263"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So to get our minds wrapped\naround how big the nucleus is,", 
            "dur": "2.821", 
            "start": "132.141"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we need to blow up the blueberry,\nup to the size of a football stadium.", 
            "dur": "3.99", 
            "start": "134.986"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So imagine a ball the size\nof a football stadium,", 
            "dur": "2.976", 
            "start": "139"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and right smack dab\nin the center of the atom,", 
            "dur": "2.976", 
            "start": "142"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you would find the nucleus,\nand you could see it!", 
            "dur": "2.334", 
            "start": "145"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And it would be the size\nof a small marble.", 
            "dur": "2.624", 
            "start": "148.278"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And there&#39;s more, if I haven&#39;t\nblown your mind by now.", 
            "dur": "2.556", 
            "start": "152.121"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s consider the atom some more.", 
            "dur": "1.62", 
            "start": "154.701"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It contains protons,\nneutrons and electrons.", 
            "dur": "2.197", 
            "start": "156.345"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The protons and neutrons\nlive inside of the nucleus,", 
            "dur": "2.429", 
            "start": "158.566"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and contain almost\nall of the mass of the atom.", 
            "dur": "2.191", 
            "start": "161.019"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Way on the edge are the electrons.", 
            "dur": "1.742", 
            "start": "163.234"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So if an atom is like a ball\nthe size of a football stadium,", 
            "dur": "2.976", 
            "start": "165"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "with the nucleus in the center,\nand the electrons on the edge,", 
            "dur": "2.905", 
            "start": "168"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "what is in between the nucleus\nand the electrons?", 
            "dur": "2.286", 
            "start": "170.929"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Surprisingly, the answer is empty space.", 
            "dur": "3.007", 
            "start": "174.104"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "(Wind noise)", 
            "dur": "2.57", 
            "start": "177.987"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That&#39;s right. Empty!", 
            "dur": "1.395", 
            "start": "180.581"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Between the nucleus and the electrons,\nthere are vast regions of empty space.", 
            "dur": "4.305", 
            "start": "182"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, technically there are\nsome electromagnetic fields,", 
            "dur": "2.572", 
            "start": "186.329"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but in terms of stuff,\nmatter, it is empty.", 
            "dur": "2.911", 
            "start": "188.925"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Remember this vast region of empty space\nis inside the blueberry,", 
            "dur": "3.523", 
            "start": "191.86"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which is inside the Earth,", 
            "dur": "1.895", 
            "start": "195.407"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which really are the atoms\nin the grapefruit.", 
            "dur": "2.185", 
            "start": "197.326"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "OK, one more thing,\nif I can even get more bizarre.", 
            "dur": "3.441", 
            "start": "199.535"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Since virtually all the mass\nof an atom is in the nucleus --", 
            "dur": "3.586", 
            "start": "203.769"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "now, there is some amount\nof mass in the electrons,", 
            "dur": "2.649", 
            "start": "207.379"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but most of it is in the nucleus --", 
            "dur": "2.021", 
            "start": "210.052"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "how dense is the nucleus?", 
            "dur": "1.772", 
            "start": "212.097"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, the answer is crazy.", 
            "dur": "1.919", 
            "start": "213.893"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The density of a typical nucleus", 
            "dur": "1.89", 
            "start": "215.836"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is four times 10 to the 17th\nkilograms per meter cubed.", 
            "dur": "3.226", 
            "start": "217.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But that&#39;s hard to visualize.\nOK, I&#39;ll put it in English units.", 
            "dur": "3.329", 
            "start": "221.615"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "2.5 times 10 to the 16th pounds\nper cubic feet.", 
            "dur": "4.008", 
            "start": "224.968"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "OK, that&#39;s still kind of hard to figure.", 
            "dur": "1.905", 
            "start": "229.864"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "OK, here&#39;s what I want you to do.", 
            "dur": "2.101", 
            "start": "231.793"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Make a box that is one foot\nby one foot by one foot.", 
            "dur": "3.524", 
            "start": "233.918"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now let&#39;s go and grab\nall of the nuclei from a typical car.", 
            "dur": "3.687", 
            "start": "237.466"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, cars on average weigh two tons.", 
            "dur": "2.334", 
            "start": "241.177"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "How many cars&#39; nuclei would you\nhave to put into the box", 
            "dur": "3.536", 
            "start": "243.535"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to have your one-foot-box have\nthe same density of the nucleus?", 
            "dur": "2.953", 
            "start": "247.095"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Is it one car? Two?", 
            "dur": "1.328", 
            "start": "250.072"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "How about 100?", 
            "dur": "1", 
            "start": "251.424"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Nope, nope and nope.", 
            "dur": "2.123", 
            "start": "253.025"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The answer is much bigger.", 
            "dur": "1.239", 
            "start": "255.825"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It is 6.2 billion.", 
            "dur": "2.795", 
            "start": "257.702"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That is almost equal to the number\nof people in the Earth.", 
            "dur": "2.893", 
            "start": "261.303"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So if everyone in the Earth\nowned their own car --", 
            "dur": "2.334", 
            "start": "264.22"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and they don&#39;t --", 
            "dur": "1.331", 
            "start": "266.578"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "(Cars honking)", 
            "dur": "1.215", 
            "start": "267.933"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and we put all of those\ncars into your box ...", 
            "dur": "2.2", 
            "start": "269.172"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That would be about\nthe density of a nucleus.", 
            "dur": "2.486", 
            "start": "273.148"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So I&#39;m saying that if you took\nevery car in the world", 
            "dur": "2.544", 
            "start": "276.909"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and put it into your one-foot box,", 
            "dur": "2.331", 
            "start": "279.477"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you would have the density of one nucleus.", 
            "dur": "2.144", 
            "start": "281.832"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "OK, let&#39;s review.", 
            "dur": "1.212", 
            "start": "284"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The atom is really,", 
            "dur": "1.66", 
            "start": "285.236"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "really, really small.", 
            "dur": "2.298", 
            "start": "286.92"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Think atoms in a grapefruit\nlike blueberries in the Earth.", 
            "dur": "3.366", 
            "start": "289.242"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The nucleus is crazy small.", 
            "dur": "2.628", 
            "start": "293.396"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now look inside the blueberry,", 
            "dur": "1.669", 
            "start": "296.048"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and blow it up to the size\nof a football stadium,", 
            "dur": "2.415", 
            "start": "297.741"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and now the nucleus\nis a marble in the middle.", 
            "dur": "2.143", 
            "start": "300.18"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The atom is made up\nof vast regions of empty space.", 
            "dur": "3.58", 
            "start": "303.417"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That&#39;s weird.", 
            "dur": "1", 
            "start": "307.608"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The nucleus has a crazy-high density.", 
            "dur": "2.22", 
            "start": "308.632"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Think of putting all those cars\nin your one-foot box.", 
            "dur": "2.477", 
            "start": "310.876"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I think I&#39;m tired.", 
            "dur": "1.308", 
            "start": "314.821"
        }
    ], 
